```
Reason:
The lack of filtering options in the constructor allows the YAML parser to instantiate any class specified by the `type` parameter, which can lead to security vulnerabilities through unsafe deserialization of arbitrary classes.

The code statements that fix the bug are:
```java
this.unmarshalType = type;
this.typeFilters = new CopyOnWriteArrayList<>();
this.typeFilters.add(TypeFilters.types(type));
```
Reason:
By introducing `typeFilters`, the patch ensures that only specified classes can be constructed during the unmarshalling process, thereby mitigating the risk of security vulnerabilities associated with arbitrary class instantiation.

